quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,84,"Say: 'We believe in God, and that which has been sent down on us, and sent down on Abraham and Ishmael, Isaac and Jacob, and the Tribes, and in that which was given to Moses and Jesus, and the Prophets, of their Lord; we make no division between any of them, and to Him we surrender"
  3,85,"Whoso desires another religion than Islam, it shall not be accepted of him; in the next world he shall be among the losers"
  3,86,"How shall God guide a people who have disbelieved after they believed, and bore witness that the Messenger is true, and the clear signs came to them? God guides not the people of the evildoers"
  3,87,"Those -- their recompense is that there shall rest on them the curse of God and of the angels and of men, altogether"
  3,88,therein dwelling forever; the chastisement shall not be lightened for them; no respite shall be given them
  3,89,"But those who repent thereafter, and make amends -- God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate"
  3,90,Surely those who disbelieve after they have believed and then increase in unbelief -- their repentance shall not be accepted; those are the ones who stray
  3,91,"Surely those who disbelieve, and die disbelieving, there shall not be accepted from any one of them the whole earth full of gold, if he would ransom himself thereby; for them awaits a painful chastisement, and they shall have no helpers"